From: Yogesh Sardana <yogesh.sardana1@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 1 Jun 2026 10:02:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] IMA: Add PKCS#11 keyring bridge for HSM-resident signing keys

This patch introduces a PKCS#11 keyring bridge that allows the IMA keyring
to reference HSM-resident (PKCS#11) signing keys without exporting key
material. This is critical for regulated environments where private keys
must never leave the HSM boundary (FIPS 140-3 Level 3+, Common Criteria
EAL4+).

The bridge provides:
- PKCS#11 URI-based key references in the IMA keyring
- On-demand signing operations via PKCS#11 C_Sign
- No key material export from the HSM
- Full audit trail for all signing operations

Signed-off-by: Yogesh Sardana <yogesh.sardana1@gmail.com>
---
